      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "YEAH YOU (3) turned spotting a big start finishing seventh (23.49) last time in a Grade 5 at Geelong. Solid record at the distance winning four races. Can make amends. TILLY GIRL (2) was safely held in tougher company last start at Sale, but prior to that won by 0.8 lengths at Sale (24.71) beating Let It Linger in a Grade 5 on March 8. Has a very good strike-rate from this draw, with two wins from four starts. Should play a prominent role. JAMS NIMBLE (1) was in the minors two back (23.31) at this track but ran below best last time at Sale, finishing 7th. Solid record here at the distance winning two races. Form from her last run is proving very strong. Can measure up this time. DREAM ON ALLAN (7) will be hard to beat with a drop in trip.",
